{
  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1939",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1939: Medium priority package update for krb5",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-07-20 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-07-20 09:00:00"
  },
  "severity": "Medium",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-11850:\n\tAn integer underflow vulnerability was found in MIT krb5 in the berval2tl_data() function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c. The function performs an unsigned subtraction (bv_len - 2) without a prior bounds check. When bv_len is 0 or 1, the subtraction wraps to a large value which is then truncated to uint16_t, yielding 0xFFFE (65534) or 0xFFFF (65535). The subsequent malloc succeeds and memcpy reads up to 65534 bytes from a 0-1 byte buffer, resulting in a heap out-of-bounds read.\nThe attack vector involves a malicious or compromised LDAP KDB backend returning a krbExtraData attribute with bv_len \u003c 2, triggering the underflow when the KDC or kadmind reads principal data.\n",
